category.description: Foodstuffs (including beverages but excluding alcoholic beverages) for human and animal consumption; live animals, seeds, plants and …

vatRateResults.comment:
- Foodstuffs referred to in article 2 in regulation EC no 178/2002 are subject to reduced VAT rate, with the exception for tap water and certain alcoholic beverages, see chapter 9 section 3 in the Swedish VAT Act.
- Goods with CN code 2203 can be subject to reduced VAT rate provided that the alcohol content is maximum 3.5 volume percent. Goods with CN code 28-29, 3201-3206, 3301-3302, 3501-3505, 3507 can be subject to reduced VAT rate if they constitute food additives.

code.description: Performing arts event production and presentation services

category.description: Admission to shows, theatres, circuses, fairs, amusement parks, concerts, museums, zoos, cinemas, exhibitions and similar cultural events and facilities

vatRateResults.comment: Admission to shows, theatres, circuses, concerts, operas, ballets and similar performances are subject to 6 % VAT. The reduced rate also applies to admission to zoos. However, arrangement of public exhibitions in museums and supplies of items to such exhibitions are exempt if the museum is run by the public sector or is supported by the public sector. Admission to amusement parks and cinemas are subject to the standard VAT rate. Please see chapter 9 section 14 in the Swedish VAT Act.
